<p>Thanks for tuning in again, folks! If you're unsatisfied with the blurb(s) provided for the article(s) you wrote, feel free to change it. Of course, you could just avoid that problem entirely by sending <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1841781&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869440" alt="A Random Day" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1841781)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;">A Random Day</a></span> or <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rumetzen" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(209204); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=209204&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869440" alt="rumetzen" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=209204)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rumetzen" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(209204); return false;">rumetzen</a></span> a blurb for your article. We may or may not use it (if we can think of something more attention-getting, though we can try to stick with one you give us) but we'd really would just like them in order to make the process easier for making these. This is a community thing, and we want authors to give their blurbs to sell these articles much easier. It reduces the workload we have to do, and helps the news come out that much earlier!</p>
